main event: A ground-based radar observation of an unknown object that appeared to move slower than a plane over Elmont, New York on July 29, 1959.
interesting points: The object was described as looking like 'moving stars' in the sky.
The observation lasted for around 30 minutes.
The report indicates there were no photographs taken of the object.
The conclusion stated there was 'Insufficient Data' to determine the nature of the sighting.
The report provides some weather details including wind speed and direction at various altitudes.
sighted object: An unknown object observed on radar
photographs: No photographs included in the report
